'''Chapel Hill''' is an [[unincorporated community]] in [[Polk Township, Monroe County, Indiana|Polk Township]], [[Monroe County, Indiana|Monroe County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]].<ref>{{cite gnis|450765|Chapel Hill, Indiana|2017-02-22}}</ref>

==History==
Chapel Hill was [[plat]]ted in 1856.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rVM0AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA435#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=History of Lawrence and Monroe Counties, Indiana: Their People, Industries, and Institutions | publisher=B.F. Bowen | year=1914 | pages=435}}</ref> The community took its name from the Chapel Hill Methodist Church located there.<ref>{{cite book|last=Baker|first=Ronald L.|title=From Needmore to Prosperity: Hoosier Place Names in Folklore and History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SXB5AAAAMAAJ|date=October 1995|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-32866-3|page=92|quote=...named for the local Chapel Hill Methodist Church.}}</ref> The community ultimately would fail to grow to its founders' expectations.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vyqC5iVmYtYC&pg=PA544#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=Counties of Morgan, Monroe and Brown, Indiana: Historical and Biographical | publisher=F.A. Battey & Company | author=Blanchard, Charles | year=1884 | pages=544}}</ref> A post office was established at Chapel Hill in 1897, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1925.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.postalhistory.com/postoffices.asp?task=display&state=IN&county=Monroe | title=Monroe County | publisher=Jim Forte Postal History | accessdate=5 September 2015}}</ref>

[[File:Pentecostal Assembly of Chapel Hill.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Pentecostal church]]

